title: ERROR    | 'Interpolator' object has no attribute 'process'
body:
When using `python -m video2x -i in.mp4 -o out.mp4 -p3 interpolate` I got following error:

```
14:09:49.503888 | INFO     | Video2X 5.0.0-beta6
14:09:49.503990 | INFO     | Copyright (C) 2018-2022 K4YT3X and contributors.
14:09:49.504029 | INFO     | Reading input video information

14:09:49.658189 | ERROR    | 'Interpolator' object has no attribute 'process'
Traceback (most recent call last):

  File "/home/adam/miniconda3/envs/env_pytorch/lib/python3.10/runpy.py", line 
196, in _run_module_as_main
    return _run_code(code, main_globals, None,
           |         |     -> {'__name__': '__main__', '__doc__': '\nCopyright 
(C) 2018-2022 K4YT3X and contributors.\n\nThis program is free software: you...
           |         -> <code object <module> at 0x7f078e376340, file 
"/home/adam/Apps/video_ai/video2x/video2x/__main__.py", line 1>
           -> <function _run_code at 0x7f07aa434f70>
  File "/home/adam/miniconda3/envs/env_pytorch/lib/python3.10/runpy.py", line 
86, in _run_code
    exec(code, run_globals)
         |     -> {'__name__': '__main__', '__doc__': '\nCopyright (C) 2018-2022
K4YT3X and contributors.\n\nThis program is free software: you...
         -> <code object <module> at 0x7f078e376340, file

  File "/home/adam/Apps/video_ai/video2x/video2x/__main__.py", line 239, in 
<module>
    sys.exit(main())
    |   |    -> <function main at 0x7f078e36ff40>
    |   -> <built-in function exit>
    -> <module 'sys' (built-in)>

> File "/home/adam/Apps/video_ai/video2x/video2x/__main__.py", line 216, in main
    video2x.interpolate(
    |       -> <function Video2X.interpolate at 0x7f078e36f6d0>
    -> <video2x.video2x.Video2X object at 0x7f078dd694e0>

  File "/home/adam/Apps/video_ai/video2x/video2x/video2x.py", line 424, in

    self._run(
    |    -> <function Video2X._run at 0x7f078e36f5b0>
    -> <video2x.video2x.Video2X object at 0x7f078dd694e0>

  File "/home/adam/Apps/video_ai/video2x/video2x/video2x.py", line 208, in _run
    processor_pool = Pool(processes, processor.process)
                     |    |          -> <Interpolator name='Interpolator-2' 
parent=13795 initial>
                     |    -> 5
                     -> <bound method BaseContext.Pool of 
<multiprocessing.context.DefaultContext object at 0x7f07aa2a73a0>>

AttributeError: 'Interpolator' object has no attribute 'process'
```

When I use standalone rife from giuthub it works without any errors, so it must be video2x problem.
